Entries.default: "It's... beautiful. I know it can kill us, captain - just let me have the moment."
"Has it been this way since the age of my ancestors?"
"I suppose we're heading straight into that."
"Hope you got a way of turning off that storm. Looks unfriendly. Mean-spirited, even."
"To think, this storm has been here since the Engwithans left Eora. Little wonder that Ukaizo has been lost for all this time."
"Don't be thinking at it too hard, cap. It be right hungry for an ill wind."
"It's even scarier than in my dreams."
